--- body ---
## Context

All sliding-window null models use Monte Carlo permutation (n_perm=500 full
Fisher-Yates shuffles of the before+after pool).  For methods where E[T | H₀]
and Var[T | H₀] have closed-form expressions (S1, S2, L1, C2ST), the
analytical values provide a ground truth to confirm that MC estimates are
unbiased and well-converged.

Rather than a standalone validation script, the analytical null is rendered
directly on the zoo figure as a second semi-transparent ribbon overlaid on
the MC ribbon.  Where MC and analytical agree, the overlapping fills merge
visually — this makes convergence immediately legible without any separate
report.

G methods (G1, G5, G6, G8) lack simple closed forms; they remain MC only.

## Permutation structure

Each (year, window) test pools n_before + n_after documents and shuffles ALL
of them (full Fisher-Yates permutation), reassigning the first n_before to
"before" and the rest to "after".

## Analytical nulls by method

### S1 — MMD²
E(MMD²_unbiased | H₀) = 0 by construction.
Var(MMD²_unbiased | H₀) ≈ (4/n²) × Var of h(X,X') under H₀ (Gretton 2012 Lemma 6).
null_mean = 0, null_std from pairwise kernel matrix O(N²).

### S2 — energy distance
null_mean from mean off-diagonal entries of pairwise distance matrix.
null_std from 4th-moment U-statistics (Székely & Rizzo 2013).  O(N²).

### L1 — JS divergence
E[JS | H₀] ≈ (V−1)/4 × (1/n_before + 1/n_after)   (Archer et al. 2014)
null_std = O(1/n).  Only requires pooled vocabulary and counts.

### C2ST — AUC
E[AUC | H₀] = 0.5 by definition of Mann-Whitney U.
Var[AUC | H₀] = (n_before + n_after + 1) / (12 × n_before × n_after)
  (Hanley & McNeil 1982).  O(1).

### G methods (G1, G5, G6, G8)
No simple closed form.  Leave analytical null undefined; overlay not shown.

## Relevant files

- `scripts/_permutation_accel.py` — add `analytical_null(method, X_before,
  X_after)` for S1 and S2
- `scripts/_permutation_lexical.py` — add analytical null for L1
- `scripts/_divergence_c2st.py` or helper — add analytical null for C2ST
- `scripts/compute_analytical_null.py` — NEW: driver; accepts --method,
  --crossyear-csv, --output; writes same CSV schema as tab_null_*.csv
  (columns: year, window, null_mean, null_std, observed)
- `scripts/plot_zoo_results.py` — add `--analytical-null <path>` flag;
  draw second semi-transparent fill_between for analytical CI band
- `divergence.mk` — add `analytical-null-*` targets; pass
  `--analytical-null` to plot_zoo_results.py when available

## Actions

1. Implement `analytical_null(method, before, after) → (null_mean, null_std)`:
   - S1, S2: in `_permutation_accel.py`
   - L1: in `_permutation_lexical.py`
   - C2ST: closed-form O(1) in `_divergence_c2st.py`

2. Write `scripts/compute_analytical_null.py`:
   - Accepts `--method`, `--crossyear-csv`, `--output`
   - Reads the crossyear CSV for (year, window) pairs + n_before/n_after
   - Calls the appropriate `analytical_null` function per row
   - Outputs CSV with same schema: year, window, null_mean, null_std, observed

3. In `plot_zoo_results.py`:
   - Add `--analytical-null <path>` (optional)
   - Load analytical null CSV if provided
   - Draw `fill_between(year, lower_analytical, upper_analytical)` with
     `alpha=0.25, color="orange"` (or similar warm colour)
   - MC ribbon keeps its existing colour at `alpha=0.25`
   - Where they overlap the combined alpha makes the coincidence visually
     distinct from regions with only one band

4. In `divergence.mk` (or `zoo.mk`):
   - Add pattern rule for `tab_analytical_null_%.csv` (methods: S1_MMD,
     S2_energy, L1, C2ST_embedding, C2ST_lexical)
   - Extend the zoo figure recipe: pass `--analytical-null` when the
     analytical null CSV is present (like the existing `--null-ci` wildcard)

## Test

Red: in `tests/test_analytical_null.py`:
- For C2ST (n_before=n_after=200, iid labels): assert analytical null_mean
  ≈ 0.5 ± 0.01 and analytical null_std matches Hanley & McNeil formula.
- For L1 (multinomial fixture, n=200, V=100): assert analytical null_mean
  ≈ (V-1)/4*(1/n₁+1/n₂) within 1%.
- For S1 (Gaussian embeddings, n=200): assert analytical null_mean ≈ 0.

## Verification

- [ ] Analytical values agree with MC (n_perm=5000) within 2 SE on fixture
- [ ] Zoo figures for S1, S2, L1, C2ST show two overlapping ribbons;
  ribbons overlap in the expected years
- [ ] MC null CSVs unchanged; analytical CSVs are separate files
- [ ] `make check-fast` passes

## Invariants

- `tab_null_*.csv` files are generated by Monte Carlo only; analytical
  values live in separate `tab_analytical_null_*.csv` files.
- G methods have no analytical null CSV; their zoo figures show only MC ribbon.
- Output CSV schema: year, window, null_mean, null_std, observed (same as MC).

## Exit criteria

- Analytical null implemented for S1, S2, L1, C2ST
- Zoo figures for those methods show overlapping MC + analytical ribbons
- Tests pass; PR merged
